<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 2:33PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Petroleum County through 300 PM MDT...
At 233 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northeast of Grass Range, or 17 miles northwest of Winnett,
moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Petroleum County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
